# AINPI analysis scripts — environment variables.
#
# Copy this file to `analysis/.env` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
# Then source it before running scripts:
#
#   set -a; source analysis/.env; set +a
#   python analysis/ingest_sam_exclusions.py
#
# The `set -a` exports every variable defined in the file; `set +a` turns
# auto-export back off. This is the cleanest no-dependency pattern.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SAM.gov Public API key — for analysis/ingest_sam_exclusions.py
#
# Get it at:    https://sam.gov/profile/details
# Field:        Public API Key (click eye icon → enter email OTP)
# Rotation:     90 days, auto-generated next key before expiry
# Permissions:  no extra role needed; basic SAM.gov account is sufficient
#
# Note: api.data.gov keys do NOT work — you need the SAM.gov-issued one.
SAM_GOV_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Cloud — usually NOT needed locally because Application Default
# Credentials kick in via `gcloud auth application-default login`. Only set
# the service-account JSON path if you're running scripts in a non-gcloud
# environment.
#
# GCP_PROJECT_ID is hardcoded in each analysis script (thematic-fort-453901-t7)
# so this var is informational only.
#
# GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY=/path/to/service-account.json
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/service-account.json
